@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Welcome to the Contract Monthly Claim System";
}

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/css/styles.css" />
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <header>
            <h1>Contract Monthly Claim System (CMCS)</h1>
        </header>

        <main>
            <section>
                <h2>Transformative Journey</h2>
                <p>
                    Embark on a transformative journey in developing the <strong>Contract Monthly Claim System (CMCS)</strong>,
                    a vital tool for streamlining the submission and approval of monthly claims for independent contractor (iC) lecturers.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>Application Features</h2>

                <div class="feature">
                    <h3>1. Claim Submission</h3>
                    <p>
                        Lecturers can submit their claims at any time with a click of a button.
                        The intuitive form allows for inputting hours worked, hourly rate, and additional notes.
                        A prominently displayed 'Submit' button makes this process straightforward.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="feature">
                    <h3>2. Claims Verification</h3>
                    <p>
                        Programme Coordinators and Academic Managers can easily verify and approve claims.
                        A dedicated view displays all pending claims, organized for clarity, with 'Approve' and 'Reject' options for each claim.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="feature">
                    <h3>3. Document Upload</h3>
                    <p>
                        Lecturers can upload supporting documents securely linked to their claims.
                        An 'Upload' button is included in the submission form, displaying the name of the uploaded file and enforcing file type restrictions.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="feature">
                    <h3>4. Claim Status Tracking</h3>
                    <p>
                        The system provides a transparent tracking system for each claim, updating status in real-time (e.g., "Pending", "Approved", "Rejected").
                        This helps users to stay informed about their claims' progress.
                    </p>
                </div>

                
            </section>

           
        </main>

        <footer>
            <p>&copy; 2024 Contract Monthly Claim System. All rights reserved.</p>
        </footer>
    </div>
</body>
</html>